race.comment: HYSTERICAL LADY (8) owns a sharp turn of foot and maps to blend into the race beautifully from the favourable draw. Now fourth-up and peaking, she shapes as the one to beat. TYUSIX (11) returned with authority at Strathalbyn, putting away a BM56 with ease. There's improvement to come and he carries next to nothing with the 3kg claimer staying aboard. A major player. BOWER BOY (6) is going far better than the form guide suggests and finally comes up with a gate. With Holder likely to have him within striking distance, he's capable of featuring. LUCAS THE YOUNGER (2) is the tough old warrior of the field, kept fresh and boasting a strong record at this track. He'll roll forward again and take plenty of catching if left alone. GRUELLING (3) chases a hat-trick and while he'll need to go to another level, he's racing too well to dismiss.
